NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|But, against most defenders, first of all South would hesitate with the Ace, and second, North might very well not duck the Ace. Therefore, at the table I would play the Queen most of the time. And since hearts are very fortunately divided, that gives Moe four heart tricks and the contract. The bottom line is, Moe should go after hearts first and then hope that the diamond finesse works if the hearts don't come in for four tricks. Again, it is a matter of counting your winners, and figuring out a plan to get to nine.|
